# Inconsistent micro-ontology — NTriples
# A is subClassOf B and also subClassOf NotB (= complementOf B).
# Any OWL-DL reasoner must report this ontology as inconsistent.

# Ontology declaration
<http://example.org/inc> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .

# Class declarations
<http://example.org/A> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://example.org/B> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://example.org/NotB> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .

# NotB is defined as the complement of B
<http://example.org/NotB> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#complementOf> <http://example.org/B> .

# A is subclass of both B and NotB → contradiction
<http://example.org/A> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://example.org/B> .
<http://example.org/A> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://example.org/NotB> .
